    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-04-16T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-04-16T17:00:00-05:00" n="65"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d65">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1099: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-04-16T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 16, 1930—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>132. Your 259, April 11, 11 a.m. Department is communicating with interested
                    mission boards through National Catholic Welfare Conference and International
                    Missionary Council urging that missions which have representatives in areas
                    where there seems to be especial danger seriously consider advisability of
                    withdrawing such representatives from exposed positions until conditions of safe
                    residence are restored.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
